    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d8492dc0_d694b07c",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 145,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-25T19:52:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I was confused by this until I learned that this method returns a const char* on error, and nullptr if everything is okay. How about something like the following:\n\n    const char* status \u003d decoder-\u003echeck_wuffs_version(...);\n    if (status) {\n        SkCodecPrintf(status);\n        *result \u003d SkCodec::kInternalError;\n        return nullptr;\n    }\n\nThat will also give us better debugging information when we have failures.\n\nSame suggestion for some other places where you check for !\u003d nullptr.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 145,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 145,
        "endChar": 91
      },
      "revId": "eac8a3e735325e1bc59d1800a4c166e147204475",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
