    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f510ecae_3db91c28",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 171,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-25T19:52:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why do you compare to INT_MAX?\n\n(Perhaps we should be consistent across our codecs; funneling them all through here would accomplish that, I suppose. Today we have some somewhat arbitrary limits for some, no limit for others.)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 171,
        "startChar": 25,
        "endLine": 171,
        "endChar": 40
      },
      "revId": "eac8a3e735325e1bc59d1800a4c166e147204475",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "04d3ae02_081a416b",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 171,
      "author": {
        "id": 8223
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-26T03:54:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Because the PNG spec has *u*int32_t width and height (https://www.w3.org/TR/2003/REC-PNG-20031110/#11IHDR), so a valid PNG image could be correctly parsed by Wuffs but should be rejected by Skia (which uses *signed* int\u0027s for width and height).\n\nYes, this CL is specifically about GIF, but the Wuffs image API aims to be format-agnostic, and allow uint32_t width and height, while always concious of integer overflow. And, in the future, it\u0027s possible to use Wuffs to decode PNGs (and other formats).",
      "parentUuid": "f510ecae_3db91c28",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 171,
        "startChar": 25,
        "endLine": 171,
        "endChar": 40
      },
      "revId": "eac8a3e735325e1bc59d1800a4c166e147204475",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ede9b838_43f03283",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 178,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-25T19:52:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why the limit of SIZE_MAX?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 178,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 178,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "eac8a3e735325e1bc59d1800a4c166e147204475",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "81a45b53_bf66bb58",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 178,
      "author": {
        "id": 8223
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-26T03:54:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Calling \"malloc(workbuf_len)\" will implicitly truncate the argument from uint64_t to size_t. Obviously, on 32 bit systems, these aren\u0027t the same types, and part of the point of Wuffs is to be careful about overflow, especially re memory.",
      "parentUuid": "ede9b838_43f03283",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 178,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 178,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "eac8a3e735325e1bc59d1800a4c166e147204475",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4ec74e7c_242b822c",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 207,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-25T19:52:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s not the only way we could end up with transparency in a later frame. If the first frame is DisposeOverwritePrevious, I think that would be the same as kRestoreBGColor. And this doesn\u0027t affect GIF, but APNG and WEBP have an option to blend with the background color.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 206,
        "startChar": 54,
        "endLine": 207,
        "endChar": 57
      },
      "revId": "eac8a3e735325e1bc59d1800a4c166e147204475",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
