    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "367a8a97_c4cb277e",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 515,
      "author": {
        "id": 8223
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-26T03:54:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The short answer is: this method has to be const, because onGetFrameInfo is const, so it cannot update fPreviousBestNumFullyReceived.\n\nThe long answer is: a Wuffs decoder runs sequentially through the input. As it proceeds, it sees (either explicitly decodes or implicitly skips) more and more frames.\n\nThe way Skia uses Wuffs, though, sometimes we seek backwards, starting a new run. Over time, there are multiple only-moves-forwards runs through the input, and some of them get further (see more frames) than others.\n\nThis method returns the highest number of frames seen, \"fully received\", either from the current run or from a previous run. We don\u0027t need to store the number of frames seen for all previous runs, only the best of all previous runs.\n\nWe don\u0027t update \"the best previous run\", aka fPreviousBestNumFullyReceived, here. We update it whenever we (potentially) seek backwards. Hence, we update it in seekFrame.\n\nI\u0027m happy to take suggestions of any comments that would make this clearer.",
      "parentUuid": "9f9d5e5b_acd321c1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 515,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 515,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "eac8a3e735325e1bc59d1800a4c166e147204475",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
