        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 611,
      "author": {
        "id": 8223
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-26T03:54:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s a Wuffs thing. If the status is incomplete, then the Wuffs decoder is suspended in a coroutine (i.e. waiting on I/O or halted on a non-recoverable error), and to keep its interal proof-of-safety invariants consistent, there\u0027s only two things you can safely do with a suspended Wuffs object: resume the coroutine, or nuke it from orbit (memset to zero and start again).\n\nA future version of Wuffs might add some mechanism to (safely) cancel a suspended coroutine, but that\u0027s probably not happening any time soon, in Wuffs v0.2.",
      "parentUuid": "d4029b7d_b79bf387",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 611,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 611,
        "endChar": 25
      },
